<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="306" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="39.[106,1096,636,691]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,228,636,660]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Etymology:</emphasis>
From the Latin 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[417,467,637,660]" class="Insecta" family="Aulacidae" genus="Pristaulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="virga">
<emphasis box="[417,467,637,660]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">virga</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, meaning stripe, referring to the striped- or banded-color pattern of the wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[106,204,721,745]" box="[106,204,721,745]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[106,204,721,745]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">Remarks:</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="39.[106,1096,759,844]" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">
This is one of three species with black-banded forewings. It is separated from the other two, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[106,217,790,813]" class="Insecta" family="Aulacidae" genus="Pristaulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="punctum">
<emphasis box="[106,217,790,813]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">P. punctum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="2008" box="[270,365,789,813]" class="Insecta" family="Aulacidae" genus="Pristaulacus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="decorus">
<emphasis box="[270,365,789,813]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="306">P. decorus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, by the entirely orange color, lack of an anteriorly projecting tooth on the pronotum, and the transverse carinae of the mesoscutum.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
